Rating: 4
Made this last night, with a few changes. Browned the pork first in a heavy pan, removed, kept warm, then added the garlic and tomatoes, deglazed with white wine, used more tapenade and thyme than called for, simmered for approximately 20 mintues. Fabulous! My fiancee and really enjoyed it with a nice rioja.